Product Version     25.10    Cadence Design Systems, Inc.
timing_context...nput_assertion(25.10)  timing_context...nput_assertion(25.10)

Name
       timing_context_apply_default_primary_input_assertion

Syntax
       timing_context_apply_default_primary_input_assertion

       {true | false}

       Default : false

       Propagates the phase at block level for unmapped clocks.

       When  set  to  true, the nets in the fanout of data ports with unmapped
       clocks are considered to have infinite timing windows during SI context
       analysis.

       When set to false, the unmapped top clock arrivals on  data  ports  are
       dropped during context analysis.

       To set this global variable, use the set command.

